{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-06",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_06_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "06 - Pig and Pepper",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.729,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 253.5,
  "page_end_sec": 496.92,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 253.5,
      "end": 255.34,
      "text": "The only things in the kitchen that did not",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 255.34,
      "end": 258.0,
      "text": "sneeze were the cook and a large cat which"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.0,
      "end": 260.44,
      "text": "was sitting on the hearth and grinning from ear to ear."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.9,
      "end": 262.5,
      "text": "Please,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 262.54,
      "end": 263.4,
      "text": "would you tell me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 263.48,
      "end": 264.96,
      "text": "said Alice a little timidly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.96,
      "end": 266.68,
      "text": "for she was not quite sure whether it"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.8,
      "end": 268.54,
      "text": "was good manners for her to speak first,"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.72,
      "end": 270.68,
      "text": "why your cat grins like that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.808,
      "end": 272.94,
      "text": "It's a Cheshire Cat,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 273.16,
      "end": 274.08,
      "text": "said the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.1,
      "end": 274.72,
      "text": "and that's why."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.16,
      "end": 275.66,
      "text": "Pig!"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.96,
      "end": 278.92,
      "text": "She said the last word with such sudden",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 278.92,
      "end": 280.62,
      "text": "violence that Alice quite jumped,"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.96,
      "end": 282.8,
      "text": "but she saw in another moment that it"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.8,
      "end": 284.7,
      "text": "was addressed to the baby and not to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.78,
      "end": 286.56,
      "text": "so she took courage and went on again."
    },
    {
      "start": 287.24,
      "end": 289.8,
      "text": "\"I didn't know that Cheshire cats always grinned;"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.88,
      "end": 290.6,
      "text": "in fact,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.66,
      "end": 292.34,
      "text": "I didn't know that cats _could_ grin.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 293.24,
      "end": 293.86,
      "text": "\"They all can,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.12,
      "end": 295.32,
      "text": "and most of 'em do."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.04,
      "end": 297.72,
      "text": "I don't know of any that do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 297.88,
      "end": 299.06,
      "text": "Alice said very politely,"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.18,
      "end": 301.64,
      "text": "feeling quite pleased to have got into a conversation."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.64,
      "end": 303.54,
      "text": "\"You don't know much,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 303.74,
      "end": 304.54,
      "text": "said the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.58,
      "end": 305.56,
      "text": "and that's a fact."
    },
    {
      "start": 307.136,
      "end": 309.2,
      "text": "Alice did not at all like the tone of this remark,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 309.38,
      "end": 311.34,
      "text": "and thought it would be as well to introduce"
    },
    {
      "start": 311.34,
      "end": 312.94,
      "text": "some other subject of conversation."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.88,
      "end": 315.48,
      "text": "While she was trying to fix on one,"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.64,
      "end": 317.88,
      "text": "the cook took the cauldron of soup off the fire,"
    },
    {
      "start": 318.2,
      "end": 320.2,
      "text": "and at once set to work throwing everything"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.2,
      "end": 322.38,
      "text": "within her reach at the Duchess and the baby."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.5,
      "end": 324.2,
      "text": "The fire irons came first,"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.36,
      "end": 326.58,
      "text": "then followed a shower of saucepans,"
    },
    {
      "start": 326.62,
      "end": 326.86,
      "text": "plates,"
    },
    {
      "start": 327.04,
      "end": 327.42,
      "text": "and dishes."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.42,
      "end": 331.18,
      "text": "The Duchess took no notice of them even when they hit her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 331.32,
      "end": 333.26,
      "text": "and the baby was howling so"
    },
    {
      "start": 333.26,
      "end": 334.84,
      "text": "much already that it was quite impossible"
    },
    {
      "start": 334.84,
      "end": 336.94,
      "text": "to say whether the blows hurt it or not."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.25,
      "end": 338.9,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 338.98,
      "end": 339.34,
      "text": "please,"
    },
    {
      "start": 339.52,
      "end": 340.38,
      "text": "mind what you're doing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.6,
      "end": 341.16,
      "text": "cried Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 341.3,
      "end": 343.14,
      "text": "jumping up and down in an agony of"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.2,
      "end": 343.4,
      "text": "terror."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.9,
      "end": 344.22,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 344.24,
      "end": 345.66,
      "text": "there goes his _precious_ nose,"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.02,
      "end": 349.36,
      "text": "as an unusually large saucepan flew close by it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.42,
      "end": 349.98,
      "text": "and very"
    },
    {
      "start": 350.06,
      "end": 351.06,
      "text": "nearly carried it off."
    },
    {
      "start": 352.26,
      "end": 354.34,
      "text": "\"If everybody minded their own business,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 354.88,
      "end": 356.46,
      "text": "the Duchess said in a hoarse growl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 356.8,
      "end": 359.48,
      "text": "the world would go round a deal faster than it does."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.98,
      "end": 362.4,
      "text": "\"Which would _not_ be an advantage,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 362.62,
      "end": 363.08,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.24,
      "end": 364.94,
      "text": "who felt very glad to get an opportunity"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.94,
      "end": 366.78,
      "text": "of showing off a little of her knowledge."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.56,
      "end": 370.12,
      "text": "Just think what work it would make with the day and the night.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 370.54,
      "end": 370.8,
      "text": "You see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 370.88,
      "end": 373.96,
      "text": "the earth takes twenty-four hours to turn round on its axis."
    },
    {
      "start": 375.392,
      "end": 376.26,
      "text": "Talking of axes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 376.64,
      "end": 377.46,
      "text": "said the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 377.48,
      "end": 378.46,
      "text": "chop off her head."
    },
    {
      "start": 379.66,
      "end": 381.64,
      "text": "Alice glanced rather anxiously at the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 381.64,
      "end": 383.44,
      "text": "cook to see if she meant to take the hint,"
    },
    {
      "start": 383.78,
      "end": 385.98,
      "text": "but the cook was busily engaged in stirring"
    },
    {
      "start": 385.98,
      "end": 388.0,
      "text": "the soup and did not seem to be listening,"
    },
    {
      "start": 388.14,
      "end": 389.92,
      "text": "so she ventured to go on again."
    },
    {
      "start": 390.92,
      "end": 391.64,
      "text": "Twenty-four hours,"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.7,
      "end": 392.18,
      "text": "I think,"
    },
    {
      "start": 392.36,
      "end": 393.18,
      "text": "or is it twelve?"
    },
    {
      "start": 393.82,
      "end": 394.12,
      "text": "I----"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.26,
      "end": 394.38,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.56,
      "end": 395.78,
      "text": "don't bother me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.08,
      "end": 397.1,
      "text": "said the Duchess."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.4,
      "end": 399.14,
      "text": "I never could abide figures."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.18,
      "end": 402.2,
      "text": "And with that she began nursing her child again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 402.48,
      "end": 404.9,
      "text": "singing a sort of lullaby to it as she did so,"
    },
    {
      "start": 405.24,
      "end": 407.88,
      "text": "and giving it a violent shake at the end of every line."
    },
    {
      "start": 409.68,
      "end": 411.44,
      "text": "\"Speak roughly to your little boy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 411.68,
      "end": 413.18,
      "text": "and beat him when he sneezes."
    },
    {
      "start": 413.7,
      "end": 415.06,
      "text": "He only does it to annoy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 415.4,
      "end": 416.86,
      "text": "because he knows it teases."
    },
    {
      "start": 418.464,
      "end": 420.5,
      "text": "CHORUS\n\n(In which the cook and the baby joined):",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 421.04,
      "end": 421.42,
      "text": "Wow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.66,
      "end": 422.02,
      "text": "wow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.04,
      "end": 422.26,
      "text": "wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 424.28,
      "end": 426.6,
      "text": "While the Duchess sang the second verse of the song,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 426.74,
      "end": 429.28,
      "text": "she kept tossing the baby violently up and down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.54,
      "end": 431.3,
      "text": "and the poor little thing howled so"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.3,
      "end": 433.14,
      "text": "that Alice could hardly hear the words."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.36,
      "end": 436.1,
      "text": "\"I speak severely to my boy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 436.32,
      "end": 438.04,
      "text": "I beat him when he sneezes."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.68,
      "end": 442.02,
      "text": "For he can thoroughly enjoy the pepper when he pleases."
    },
    {
      "start": 442.86,
      "end": 443.36,
      "text": "\"Wow,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 443.6,
      "end": 443.96,
      "text": "wow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.96,
      "end": 444.2,
      "text": "wow.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 445.72,
      "end": 446.22,
      "text": "\"Here!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 446.42,
      "end": 448.02,
      "text": "you may nurse it a bit if you like!"
    },
    {
      "start": 448.34,
      "end": 449.76,
      "text": "the duchess said to Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 450.08,
      "end": 451.76,
      "text": "flinging the baby at her as she spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.52,
      "end": 455.06,
      "text": "\"I must go and get ready to play croquet with the Queen,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 456.06,
      "end": 457.4,
      "text": "And she hurried out of the room."
    },
    {
      "start": 457.82,
      "end": 460.28,
      "text": "The cook threw a frying pan after her as she went out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 460.68,
      "end": 461.7,
      "text": "but it just missed her."
    },
    {
      "start": 463.04,
      "end": 464.92,
      "text": "Alice caught the baby with some difficulty,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.28,
      "end": 467.44,
      "text": "as it was a queer-shaped little creature and"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.44,
      "end": 469.4,
      "text": "held out its arms and legs in all directions."
    },
    {
      "start": 470.18,
      "end": 471.2,
      "text": "\"just like a star-fish,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 471.34,
      "end": 471.8,
      "text": "thought Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 472.64,
      "end": 474.92,
      "text": "The poor little thing was snorting like a steam engine"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.92,
      "end": 475.82,
      "text": "when she caught it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.88,
      "end": 477.88,
      "text": "and kept doubling itself up and"
    },
    {
      "start": 477.88,
      "end": 479.72,
      "text": "straightening itself out again so that"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.78,
      "end": 480.16,
      "text": "altogether,"
    },
    {
      "start": 480.44,
      "end": 481.58,
      "text": "for the first minute or two,"
    },
    {
      "start": 482.22,
      "end": 484.2,
      "text": "it was as much as she could do to hold it."
    },
    {
      "start": 485.16,
      "end": 487.9,
      "text": "As soon as she had made out the proper way of nursing it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 487.98,
      "end": 489.94,
      "text": "which was to twist it up into a knot"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.1,
      "end": 492.1,
      "text": "and then keep tight hold of its right ear and"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.1,
      "end": 494.6,
      "text": "left foot so as to prevent its undoing itself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.16,
      "end": 496.92,
      "text": "she carried it out into the open air."
    }
  ]
}